Section 1:
1 L.D. 326
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 226, L.D. 326, “An Act to Increase the
10 Property Tax Exemption Provided to Individuals Who Are Legally Blind”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §654-A, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2019, c. 401, Pt. A, §8, is
13 further amended to read:
14 1. Exemption. The residential real estate up to the just value of $4,000 $6,000, having
15 a taxable situs in the place of residence, of inhabitants of the State who are legally blind as
16 determined by a properly licensed Doctor of Medicine, Doctor of Osteopathy or Doctor of
17 Optometry is exempt from taxation.
18 The State shall reimburse a municipality 50% of the property tax revenue loss suffered by
19 that municipality during the previous calendar year as a result of the exemption specified
20 in this subsection in accordance with the procedure in section 661.'
21 Amend the bill by inserting after section 2 the following:
22 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
23 allocations are made.
24 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
25 Revenue Services, Bureau of 0002
26 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for computer programming costs.
27 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
28 All Other $0 $29,480
29 __________ __________
30 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $29,480
3217 '
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR0657(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 226, L.D. 326
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment changes the amount of the property tax exemption in the bill to $6,000
33 and requires the State to reimburse a municipality 50% of the property tax revenue loss due
44 to the exemption. It also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
55 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
66 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0657(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
